Intro: ProPublica's COMPAS analysis¶

  • ProPublica obtained records for nearly 12,000 defendants in Broward County, Fla., who were assigned a COMPAS score in 2013-2014.
  • ProPublica then determined which defendants were charged with new crimes in the subsequent two years, and made this data set publicly available.

Correct ProPublica Two-Year Dataset¶

No. of rows in ProPublica's original dataset: 7214
No. of rows in corrected dataset: 6216

Data preprocessing & Feature Engineering¶

Feature Engineering: c_charge_degree_detailed¶

We ranked the degree of crime in 5 categories according to Florida law:

  • M1: Misdemeanours type 1 (simple Battery, Shoplifting, Prostitution, ...)
  • M2: Misdemeanours type 2 (simple assault, driving with a suspended license, ...)
  • F3: Third degree Felony (illegal drug possession, burglary, drive under influence, ...)
  • F2: Second degree Felony (aggravated battery with a weapon, sexual battery, ...)
  • F1: First degree Felony (robbery with a weapon, human trafficking, ...)

Feature selection¶

  • Feature correlation
  • Feature permutation (MDA)
  • Impurity reduction (MDI)
  • Forward- and backward-feature selection (SequentialFeatureSelector)

Feature correlation¶

  • High correlation redundant information
  • Pearson's correlation heatmap:

Feature permutation (MDA)¶

  • Subset with age and c_charge_degree_detailed more important features
  • Removing age_cat and c_charge_degree increase of overall feature importance

Comparison subset with and without race as a feature¶

  • including race as a feature further increase of overall importance of the different features
  • train another pair of models on race subset

Classification - Model iteration¶

Overview Classification models¶

Models we created. Each exists in two versions with and without feature "race":

  • Baseline Model (DummyClassifier)
  • Logistic Regression:
    • untuned & tuned
  • Single Tree Models:
    • single "vanilla" Tree Model
    • Single hyperparameter-tuned Tree Model
  • Bagged Tuned Decision Tree
  • Random Forests:
    • Untuned Random Forest
    • Tuned Random Forest
  • XGB Boosting Classifiers:
    • Untuned XGB Boosting Classifier
    • Tuned XGB Boosting Classifier

Classification - Cross validated scores of best models¶

  • feature "race" is included
  • XGBoost: highest roc_auc, highest recall, lowest log_loss
  • tuned single tree: highest accuracy, precision, f1 score

What can we improve to make the models less biased?¶

Historical Dataset:

  • Question the origin of the Data

Measure of Success:

  • Question the criteria of success
